8 SECTION 1. (1) The Oregon Statewide Preparedness Authority for Response Training and
9 Intergovernmental Continuity of Imperative Services is established as an office within the
10 Oregon Department of Administrative Services. The office is to be known as and may be
11 cited as SPARTICIS.
12 (2) The office is under the supervision and control of the State Resilience Officer, who
13 is responsible for the performance of the duties, functions and powers of the office.
14 (3) For purposes of administration, the State Resilience Officer may organize and reor-
15 ganize the office and appoint administrative personnel as the State Resilience Officer con-
16 siders necessary to properly conduct the work of the office.
17 (4) The State Resilience Officer may divide the functions of the office into administrative
18 divisions. The State Resilience Officer may appoint an individual to administer each division.
19 The administrator of each division serves at the pleasure of the State Resilience Officer and
20 is not subject to the provisions of ORS chapter 240. Each individual appointed under this
21 subsection must be well qualified by technical training and experience in the functions to be
22 performed by the individual.
