13 SECTION 23. ORS 401.913 is amended to read:
14 401.913. (1) The office of State Resilience Officer is created in the office of the Governor. The
15 office of State Resilience Officer shall direct, implement and coordinate hazard safety and resilience
16 goal setting and state agency planning and preparation to improve hazard safety and resilience, in-
17 cluding but not limited to planning and preparation for safety and resilience during and after
18 earthquake, tsunami, wildfire, flooding and other natural or manmade events.
19 (2) The State Resilience Officer shall lead statewide efforts to implement the Oregon Resilience
20 Plan, the Natural Hazard Mitigation Plan and other resilience plans adopted by the state.
21 (3) The State Resilience Officer shall facilitate policy standardization among state agen-
22 cies, prioritize investments for improving resilience posture and provide regular reports on
23 state agency resilience policy compliance, organizational preparedness, continuity of
24 governance procedures and measures of emergency readiness. Such reports may be made to
25 the Governor, appropriate committees of the Legislative Assembly or relevant public safety
26 advisory boards and commissions.
27 [(3)] (4) The State Resilience Officer shall lead executive branch agencies in continuity of op-
28 erations planning and continuity of government planning.
29 [(4)] (5) The Governor shall appoint an individual to serve as the State Resilience Officer, sub-
30 ject to confirmation by the Senate pursuant to Article III, section 4, of the Oregon Constitution.
31 [(5)] (6) The legislative branch of government and the judicial branch of government shall each
32 select an individual to monitor the effectiveness of hazard safety and resilience planning in their
