37 SECTION 24. (1) The Oregon Disaster Recovery Authority is established as an advisory
38 group within the Office of the Governor to direct emergency recovery in Oregon. The Gov-
39 ernor shall determine the membership of the authority, subject to subsection (2) of this
40 section.
41 (2) The Governor shall appoint at least eight individuals to serve as members of the au-
42 thority from among state agency leadership, local emergency managers and others with ex-
43 pertise in emergency management. The Governor shall seek the advice of the Oregon
44 Homeland Security Council when making appointments to the authority. Members of the
45 authority serve at the pleasure of the Governor.
[9]

HB 4121
1 (3) If the Governor declares a state of emergency under ORS 401.165, the Governor may
2 activate the authority. The authority remains activated until deactivated by order of the
3 Governor. The authority may remain activated notwithstanding the termination of a state
4 of emergency.
5 (4) When activated, the authority shall:
6 (a) Coordinate initial crisis services;
7 (b) Coordinate recovery and mitigation efforts throughout this state, using a framework
8 aligned with emergency support functions as defined by the Federal Emergency Management
9 Agency; and
10 (c) Coordinate the provision of emergency funding and other aid to local governments or
11 private entities.
12 (5) A majority of the members of the authority constitutes a quorum for the transaction
13 of business.
14 (6) Official action by the authority requires the approval of a majority of the members
15 of the authority.
