17 person.
18 (8) The authority shall meet at times and places specified by the call of the Governor or
19 the chairperson. The authority may meet at times when the authority is not activated to
20 maintain readiness in the event of an emergency.
21 (9) The authority may adopt rules necessary for the operation of the authority.
22 (10) The Office of the Governor shall provide staff support to the authority.
23 (11) Members of the authority are not entitled to compensation or reimbursement for
24 expenses and serve as volunteers on the authority.
25 (12) All agencies of state government, as defined in ORS 174.111, are directed to assist
26 the authority in the performance of the duties of the authority and, to the extent permitted
27 by laws relating to confidentiality, to furnish information and advice the members of the
28 authority consider necessary to perform their duties.
29 SECTION 25. (1) If the Oregon Disaster Recovery Authority established under section 24
30 of this 2026 Act is activated pursuant to a declaration of emergency, the Governor may hire
31 additional state agency personnel under this section.
32 (2) Additional personnel hired under this section:
33 (a) May be placed at any state agency, including the Office of the Governor;
34 (b) Must perform duties related to the emergency, which may include taking over duties
35 previously performed by other state agency personnel who have been reassigned to
36 emergency-related tasks; and
37 (c) Must have their employment terminated no later than the date the authority is de-
38 activated under section 24 of this 2026 Act.
39 (3) Notwithstanding any other law relating to state government employment, additional
40 personnel hired under this section may be recruited and selected through any means the
